FOODBORNE ILLNESS - TURKEY: (KONYA) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 2 Feb 2022
Source: Saglik Aktuel [in Turkish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.saglikaktuel.com/haber/konyada-30-universite-ogrencisi-zehirlenme-suphesiyle-hastanelere-kaldirildi-81110.htm


A total of 30 university students who were allegedly poisoned by the food they ate in Konya were taken to hospitals. Some of the students who ate at the KTO Karatay University cafeteria in the central Karatay district, Akabe District, complained of nausea and dizziness. Thereupon, university officials asked for help from the 112 Emergency Service team. It was learned that 30 students, who were taken to hospitals with the suspicion of food poisoning, were in good health.

In the statement made by KTO Karatay University, "It was seen that some people were affected due to a meal in our university cafeteria, and medical attention was given quickly. It is important that our students and valuable educators who feel unwell because of the food they consume in our university cafeteria contact us quickly."

--
Communicated by:
Mahmoud Orabi
